column5: Advanced Taxidermy...  I wonder if they will have it at the show???       They are auctioning them off... more info here..  http://www.ofncommunity.com/forums/index.php?showtopic=40480
That should be hanging on a wall...too beautiful to actually use as a lure...nice!!
absolutely amazing!!
oh my, oh my my my  my bidding finger is getting real itchy. I have a small 8" desk top muskie they did a number of years ago. Advanced is definitely in a class by their own.
wow I just might catch a muskie with that thing
I forgot this picture...

I've actually inquired  for  them to paint some custom lures. I will see them at the show to see if they still can. Hope he says yes.
Are you aloud to use a walleye lure that is in the slot???  My mouth started to water just looking at that lure... little salt, pepper and a lemon wedge mmmmmm.
WOW! that is very impressive
Wow the Detail is amazing
Thats one hot lure lure. Should call it the Underwood.
That looks like a skin mount!  Beautiful!

The boys at advance taxidermy are true artists, if anybody wants a mount made these are the dudes to get your work done. not only will you get an unbeleivable recreation of your fish you'll also have a piece of art
beauty artwork. its for wall hanging. its not designed to run. the lip and screw angle are wrong. . definatly an amazing piece

This is one of the examples of a limited edition set that the boys are producing to support a great cause for Shawn's son Chase. They will be creating 10 numbered lures in 6 different designs... they will be Walleye (as seen) blue walleye, bluegill, smallmouth, largemouth and perch.  For the collector that loves limited edition fishing related goodies and a great cause this is all of that. I don't think these will last too long once they get them going.  JP
WOW those are amazing
One of them in a 2-3" size would be a sweet key chain.

I'm pretty sure a custom paint job will cost the same as a custom replica. Minus the lure itself which isnt much. Sean has had a few ideas of lure making over the years but lure maknig is not a great business.   I hope he does well for Chase.
